Only public auction sales count. The work must be a painting, and the amount must meet or exceed US\$100,000,000 as reported by the auction house. Private sales do not count.

If a single sale price is reported by the auction house, then that price will be used for resolution. If the auction house reports hammer prices and buyer's fees (explained [here](https://www.barnebys.com/blog/auctions-101-hammer-price-vs.-buyers-premium)) separately, then both will be summed for resolution.&#x20;

For purposes of this question, a “painting” is a work categorized by the auction house as a painting in its official sale listing, press release, or other public pronouncements.
